<p><b>Michael Bruce Sterling</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1954-04-14"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-14"><a href="/wiki/April_14" title="April 14">April 14</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1954" title="1954">1954</a></span>) is an American <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction_author" title="Science fiction author" class="mw-redirect">science fiction author</a>, best known for his novels and his seminal work on the <i><a href="/wiki/Mirrorshades_(book)" title="Mirrorshades (book)" class="mw-redirect">Mirrorshades</a></i> anthology, which helped define the <a href="/wiki/Cyberpunk" title="Cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a> genre.</p>
